stylometry: Integer programming models offer yes or no answers by showing a 0 or 1 in the solution. For each problem there are two to the tenth power of solutions, which is a ton of solutions. The algorithm handles it different because instead of an exact number there is a yes or no answer. An example of a integer programming model we did in class was the Textile Manufacturing. In that model we figured out whether or not to produce certain clothing items to maximize sales.We have to consider when Excel is dealing with 0,1 models is that depending on the amount of time we set for the computer to solve, as well as the percentage we set for it to get within the optimum solution of the problem can greatly affect the results. When we did this problem is class, several people got different answers because thier solver settings were set differently.
